Bluetongue, Tunisia
-------------------
Information received on 21 Oct 2009 from Mr Malek Zrelli, Directeur
General des Services Veterinaires , Direction Generale des Services
Veterinaires, Ministere de l'agriculture, de l'environnement et des
ressources hydrauliques, TUNIS, Tunisia
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date 05 Sep 2009
Date of first confirmation of the event 07 Oct 2009
Report date 21 Oct 2009
Date submitted to OIE 21 Oct 2009
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence June 2008
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus Serotype 1
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to: a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Sidi Salem, Om Adham, Sidi Bouzid Ouest, SIDI BOUZID
Date of start of the outbreak 05 Sep 2009
Outbreak status: Resolved (16 Oct 2009)
Epidemiological unit; Farm
Species Sheep
Susceptible 150
Cases 10
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Affected Population: Young animals

Outbreak 2 Saddaguia, Saddaguia, Sidi Bouzid Ouest, SIDI BOUZID
Date of start of the outbreak 07 Sep 2009
Outbreak status: Resolved (14 Oct 2009)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Species Sheep
Susceptible 400
Cases 4
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Affected Population: Young animals

Outbreak 3 Abdelssadek, Abdessadek, Sened, GAFSA
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Sep 2009
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Species Sheep
Susceptible 60
Cases 5
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Affected Population: Young animals

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected
Species Sheep
Susceptible 610
Cases 19
Deaths 0
