Slaughtered 0

Outbreak statistics
Species Sheep
Apparent morbidity rate 3.11 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.00 percent
Apparent case fatality rate
Proportion susceptible animals lost*
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology: Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection.
Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Occurrence of the disease in the centre of
the country near humid areas.

Control measures Measures applied - Control of arthropods. Screening;
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); No vaccination
Treatment of affected animals (Symptomatic treatment)
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Laboratory name and type
Veterinary Research Institute of Tunisia (National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species Sheep
Test luminescence immunoassay
Test date 07 Oct 2009
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The outbreaks in Tunisia are caused by the serotype BTV-1, which
caused the outbreaks earlier in the year in Algeria and also earlier
this month in Morocco. Vaccination of highly valued stock should be
considered. BTV-1 has also recently been seen in the Eastern
Mediterranean in Lesbos, Greece and in Oman. See comments of Mod.AS
in ProMED-mail posting No. 20090916.3249. - Mods.FE/PC]

[The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive maps of Tunisia showing Sidi
Bouzid and Gafsa regions respectively are available at:
<http://healthmap.org/r/00Xi> and
<http://healthmap.org/r/00Xj>
- Mod.FE]
